Title: General Door Item (including Gate, Roller Shutter)
Doors (Revit Family)
Subtitle: Family Category
Description:
Model Author: Contractor

1. Diversification by type and schedule
2. No mirroring; handing is as per schedule
3. Hosted in Arch model, in correct wall layer/skin (e.g. masonry), host wall C/M to Struc Engineer's model (openings persistent).
4. Opening direction to code
5. Set to correct side of wall
6. Door numbering to reflect location by level/room
7. Hardware not modelled, but specified in door schedule and properties (refer FM Data requirements)
8. Tolerance applies to position in host wall, not to size of door or frame.

Title: Data Devices (Revit Family)
Description:
Model Author: Contractor

1. Diversification by type and schedules
2. Symbolic (2D) plan representation suitable for object recognition
3. Proprietary items to be modelled indicatively so as not to exceed overall dimensions of unit/type specified
4. Some finer details that do not affect coordination are disregarded
5. Fixtures to be modelled and located in nominal positions - and grouped
6. Wiring between devices to be shown indicatively using 2D detail linework, also grouped
7. Mounting heights of fixtures to be referenced to FFL, positioned coplanar with ceiling or wall surface (not hosted)
